                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.5051/9–1344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 13, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1574. Reference Department’s telegram No. 1088, September 9, 4 p.m.<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d855fn68">Not printed.</note> Dr. Roberto Urdaneta, Counsel to
                    Rubber Development Corporation, informs me that yesterday he saw Secretary
                    General of the Foreign Office.<note n="69" xml:id="d855fn69">Francisco Umana
                        Bernal.</note> According to Urdaneta, Umana Bernal had sent a letter to
                    Judge pointing out the official character of Rubber Development as confirmed by
                    exchange of notes between the two Governments. Urdaneta said that if Umana’s
                    letter did not produce lifting of embargo of Rubber Development’s funds Attorney
                    General would be requested to take legal steps before the court.</p>
                <p>The foregoing information was conveyed to me by Foreign Minister last
                    evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
